text: Acrobasis porphyrella is a moth of the family Pyralidae. It is known from Spain, Portugal, France, Corsica, Sardinia, the Balearic Islands, Italy and Croatia. The larvae feed on Erica arborea and Erica scoparia. ==References== Category:Moths described in 1836 Category:Acrobasis Category:Moths of Europe
title: Acrobasis porphyrella
